README.md
     1â†’semver(1) -- The semantic versioner for npm
     4â†’## Install
     6â†’```bash
     7â†’npm install semver
     8â†’````
     9â†’
    10â†’## Usage
    12â†’As a node module:
    13â†’
    14â†’```js
    15â†’const semver = require('semver')
    16â†’
    17â†’semver.valid('1.2.3') // '1.2.3'
    18â†’semver.valid('a.b.c') // null
    19â†’semver.clean('  =v1.2.3   ') // '1.2.3'
    20â†’semver.satisfies('1.2.3', '1.x || >=2.5.0 || 5.0.0 - 7.2.3') // true
    21â†’semver.gt('1.2.3', '9.8.7') // false
    22â†’semver.lt('1.2.3', '9.8.7') // true
    23â†’semver.minVersion('>=1.0.0') // '1.0.0'
    24â†’semver.valid(semver.coerce('v2')) // '2.0.0'
    25â†’semver.valid(semver.coerce('42.6.7.9.3-alpha')) // '42.6.7'
    26â†’```
    27â†’
    28â†’You can also just load the module for the function that you care about if
    29â†’you'd like to minimize your footprint.
    30â†’
    31â†’```js
      â†’â€¦
   139â†’## Versions
   141â†’A "version" is described by the `v2.0.0` specification found at
   142â†’<https://semver.org/>.
   143â†’
   144â†’A leading `"="` or `"v"` character is stripped off and ignored.
   145â†’Support for stripping a leading "v" is kept for compatibility with `v1.0.0` of the SemVer
   146â†’specification but should not be used anymore.
   147â†’
   148â†’## Ranges
   150â†’A `version range` is a set of `comparators` that specify versions
   151â†’that satisfy the range.
   152â†’
   153â†’A `comparator` is composed of an `operator` and a `version`.  The set
   154â†’of primitive `operators` is:
   155â†’
   156â†’* `<` Less than
   157â†’* `<=` Less than or equal to
   158â†’* `>` Greater than
   159â†’* `>=` Greater than or equal to
   160â†’* `=` Equal.  If no operator is specified, then equality is assumed,
   161â†’  so this operator is optional but MAY be included.
   162â†’
   163â†’For example, the comparator `>=1.2.7` would match the versions
   164â†’`1.2.7`, `1.2.8`, `2.5.3`, and `1.3.9`, but not the versions `1.2.6`
   165â†’or `1.1.0`. The comparator `>1` is equivalent to `>=2.0.0` and
   166â†’would match the versions `2.0.0` and `3.1.0`, but not the versions
   167â†’`1.0.1` or `1.1.0`.
   168â†’
   169â†’Comparators can be joined by whitespace to form a `comparator set`,
      â†’â€¦
   184â†’### Prerelease Tags
   219â†’#### Prerelease Identifiers
   250â†’#### Prerelease Identifier Base
   279â†’### Advanced Range Syntax
   287â†’#### Hyphen Ranges `X.Y.Z - A.B.C`
   306â†’#### X-Ranges `1.2.x` `1.X` `1.2.*` `*`
   324â†’#### Tilde Ranges `~1.2.3` `~1.2` `~1`
   341â†’#### Caret Ranges `^1.2.3` `^0.2.5` `^0.0.4`
   384â†’### Range Grammar
   408â†’## Functions
   410â†’All methods and classes take a final `options` object argument.  All
   411â†’options in this object are `false` by default.  The options supported
   412â†’are:
   413â†’
   414â†’- `loose`: Be more forgiving about not-quite-valid semver strings.
   415â†’  (Any resulting output will always be 100% strict compliant, of
   416â†’  course.)  For backwards compatibility reasons, if the `options`
   417â†’  argument is a boolean value instead of an object, it is interpreted
   418â†’  to be the `loose` param.
   419â†’- `includePrerelease`: Set to suppress the [default
   420â†’  behavior](https://github.com/npm/node-semver#prerelease-tags) of
   421â†’  excluding prerelease tagged versions from ranges unless they are
   422â†’  explicitly opted into.
   423â†’
   424â†’Strict-mode Comparators and Ranges will be strict about the SemVer
   425â†’strings that they parse.
   426â†’
   427â†’* `valid(v)`: Return the parsed version, or null if it's not valid.
   428â†’* `inc(v, releaseType, options, identifier, identifierBase)`: 
   429â†’  Return the version incremented by the release
      â†’  â€¦
